# JavaScript conventions

Follow `.eslintrc` (airbnb-base) and `.editorconfig`.

## Style

- 4-space indent, LF, max line length 150
- ES6 modules in `src/`: `import`/`export`, `export default` for primary classes
- PascalCase classes, camelCase functions and variables
- JSDoc on public classes and constructor `options`

## Patterns

- Stream classes extend `Transform` with `{ objectMode: true }`
- Respect backpressure: check `.write()` return value and listen for `drain`
- Template modules are pure functions; re-export from `src/templates/index.js`
- Route all user string content through `sanitize()` from `utils.js`

## Example

```javascript
export default class XLSXRowTransform extends Transform {
    constructor(shouldFormat) {
        super({ objectMode: true });
        this.shouldFormat = shouldFormat;
    }

    _transform(row, encoding, callback) {
        if (!Array.isArray(row)) return callback();
        callback(null, Row(this.rowCount++, row, this.shouldFormat));
    }
}
```

Do not introduce TypeScript source files unless the project migrates; `tsc` only compiles existing JS to `dist/`.
